commit ee506f0722292f40adf234d21064da66d22baf29
Author: Meekness Adesina <zenon8adams@gmail.com>
Date:   Wed Dec 27 23:26:17 2023 +0100

    Source/fix: Drag extending past monitor size
    
    When a small image is loaded and the edge of the
    image viewer is dragged or moved, it extends past
    the bounding edge of the active monitor.
    
    Close button color has been updated to a brighter
    color.
    
    Signed-off-by: Meekness Adesina <zenon8adams@gmail.com>

commit 624ed99e187b3d3152acc0da27017e88dbfb4620
Author: Meekness Adesina <zenon8adams@gmail.com>
Date:   Sat Dec 23 14:46:24 2023 +0100

    Source/Minor: Improve startup time for pixzzle
    
    The time it takes for the shot tool to be activated
    has been improved by implementing thumbnail cache.
    The caching system saves a thumbnail image the
    first time the image is loaded into the
    `ThumbnailViewer`. This is the file/image that is
    loaded at every other time.
    
    We also save an indicator as an ancilliary chunk
    in the png screenshot that assists us in determining
    which thumbnail ought to be blurred. Thumbnails
    smaller in size than the `ThumbnailViewer`'s size
    are always blurred.
    
    Signed-off-by: Meekness Adesina <zenon8adams@gmail.com>

commit 2ae9e1f5bb83fa67c40959f34ef50e5ee4c9d3f5
Author: Meekness Adesina <zenon8adams@gmail.com>
Date:   Wed Dec 20 10:16:03 2023 +0100

    Source/Minor: Load shots based on order taken
    
    Make sure to arrange all screenshots in the
    thumbnail based on order in which it was
    taken. Also the first shot shown in big view
    is same as the latest shot taken.
    
    Signed-off-by: Meekness Adesina <zenon8adams@gmail.com>

commit 274697ebb7b48ace491094634ab872a442636704
Author: Meekness Adesina <zenon8adams@gmail.com>
Date:   Wed Dec 20 09:20:12 2023 +0100

    Source/Fix: Window vertical expansion glitch
    
    When the window is dragged vertically and it hits
    the top and bottom boundary, it tends to bounce
    irregularly around that boundary giving off visual
    artifacts. To fix this, we use only update some
    endpoints based on if we are in drag mode or resize
    mode.
    
    Remove registered signal handlers for the `shutter`.
    
    Signed-off-by: Meekness Adesina <zenon8adams@gmail.com>

commit 8251ee0fa6ded455b50be70071cf4f2963df8b9f
Author: Meekness Adesina <zenon8adams@gmail.com>
Date:   Sat Dec 9 18:32:45 2023 +0100

    Source/feat: Implement copying of current image
    
    User can use Ctrl+C and Ctrl+Shift+C to copy
    the current image in the big view. Ctrl+C copies
    the whole image, Ctrl+Shift+C copies the section
    currently visible in the viewport.
    
    Fixed issues pointed out by gnome reviewer in
    preparation for alpha-v2 release. This includes:
    - Removal of deprecated modules
    - Disposal of connection handlers
    - Removal of incompatible library imports
    - Proper initialization of translation
    
    Fix issue regarding vertical expansion glitch.
    When the window is dragged such that it touches
    both ends of the screen. It extends out of its
    containing view.
    
    Signed-off-by: Meekness Adesina <zenon8adams@gmail.com>

