commit cffb0f2e718d61c7a892c580ad6e07e856e60348
Author: Meekness Adesina <zenon8adams@gmail.com>
Date:   Fri Nov 17 02:49:15 2023 +0100

    Source/feat: Support for custom theming and config
    
    Nearly all sections of the main viewer can be customized
    to suit user's taste. The keybinding for toggling
    pixzzle can be changed from the default. Any key combo
    can be bound other than the page rotation control keys
    `Ctrl+R` and `Ctrl+L`. A reset button is also provided
    to restore user to original installation theme in case
    theming goes wrong. Directional panning control is also
    a customizable property for users preferring alternate
    panning direction other than natural.
    
    Gnome's top panel has been accounted for during dragging
    of the viewer. We don't allow pixzzle to expand past the
    top panel.
    
    Signed-off-by: Meekness Adesina <zenon8adams@gmail.com>

