commit db0c3494b412e37c47c7d2bc5d1162a575499f3d
Author: Meekness Adesina <zenon8adams@gmail.com>
Date:   Mon Nov 13 02:28:33 2023 +0100

    Source/feat: Implement page rotation
    
    The orientation of pages can be changed
    by pressing Ctrl+R for clockwise rotation
    and Ctrl+L for anti-clockwise rotation.
    Each orientation keeps track of the
    current panning state. Panning to position
    before rotation restores the panned state
    on returning to the same orientation.
    
    Setup rotation animation for the settings
    button giving live to the MainViewer.
    
    The MainViewer has been configured to be
    constrained by the position of the gnome
    panel. The `Expand` indicator has been
    modified to follow suite.
    
    Signed-off-by: Meekness Adesina <zenon8adams@gmail.com>

