    The upscale window crashes as a result
    of repeated reconstruction of
    `Clutter.ImageContent` element. This
    has been superseded by `Clutter.Canvas`.
    
    The wrong comment about BlurEffect has
    been removed and replaced with
    `Shell.BlurEffect`.
    
    Signed-off-by: Meekness Adesina <zenon8adams@gmail.com>

commit 5073d5d8868c55ad747bd978beea6181d33d571c
Author: Meekness Adesina <zenon8adams@gmail.com>
Date:   Thu Nov 2 23:29:17 2023 +0100

    Source/Minor: Build separate thumbnail view
    
    The UI has been redesigned with a new idea of
    thumbnails. Each shots taken are stored
    in the `USER_CACHE_DIR` which resolves
    to ~/.cache on debian. These are loaded into
    a viewport which displays a tiny thumbnail.
    Any of the entries in the side view when
    clicked, expands into a bigger view pane.
    
    Upcoming:
        - Implement a smarter expansion mechanism
          for the side view. Currently, the
          view expands in an horrible manner.
        - Improve hacks in code.
    
    Signed-off-by: Meekness Adesina <zenon8adams@gmail.com>

commit c2c422dd2019b233d9d6480d3c424993a444e6bc
Author: Meekness Adesina <zenon8adams@gmail.com>
Date:   Tue Oct 31 22:37:57 2023 +0100

    Source/feat: Connect main-view with shutter-view
    
    By clicking on the `Add New` button, the user
    will transition into the view to take a new shot
    and back to the main view if exit controls are
    triggered from the shutter view.
    
    `.prettierrc` formatting style guide has been
    added.
    
    The cursor restoration issue has been fixed.
    See @985959
    
    Signed-off-by: Meekness Adesina <zenon8adams@gmail.com>

